T1  - Agency Models With Frequent Actions
AU  - Sadzik, Tomasz
AU  - Stacchetti, Ennio
Y1  - 2015/01/01
PY  - 2015
DA  - 2015/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10656
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 193
EP  - 237
VL  - 83
IS  - 1
KW  - Principal–agent model
KW  - imperfect monitoring
KW  - frequent actions
KW  - quadratic approximation
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10656
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - The paper analyzes dynamic principal?agent models with short period lengths. The two main contributions are: (i) an analytic characterization of the values of optimal contracts in the limit as the period length goes to 0, and (ii) the construction of relatively simple (almost) optimal contracts for fixed period lengths. Our setting is flexible and includes the pure hidden action or pure hidden information models as special cases. We show how such details of the underlying information structure affect the optimal provision of incentives and the value of the contracts. The dependence is very tractable and we obtain sharp comparative statics results. The results are derived with a novel method that uses a quadratic approximation of the Pareto boundary of the equilibrium value set.
ER  - 

