T1  - Trade Dynamics in the Market for Federal Funds
AU  - Afonso, Gara
AU  - Lagos, Ricardo
Y1  - 2015/01/01
PY  - 2015
DA  - 2015/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10586
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 263
EP  - 313
VL  - 83
IS  - 1
KW  - Fed funds market
KW  - search
KW  - bargaining
KW  - over-the-counter market
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10586
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We develop a model of the market for federal funds that explicitly accounts for its two distinctive features: banks have to search for a suitable counterparty, and once they meet, both parties negotiate the size of the loan and the repayment. The theory is used to answer a number of positive and normative questions: What are the determinants of the fed funds rate? How does the market reallocate funds? Is the market able to achieve an efficient reallocation of funds? We also use the model for theoretical and quantitative analyses of policy issues facing modern central banks.
ER  - 

